If Statement Explained!

ok to start i will show you an if statement and explain it in better detail :)

   [code]if(playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("Carn Carn") && playerRights >= 1) {
	teleportToX = 241;
	teleportToY = 241;
	else if(playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("D E C O Y") && isNoob() == true)
	{
	 CanhaveChildren == False;
	}
	}[/code]

ok now to explain ^.^

the first line [i]if(playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("carney") && playerRights >= 1)[/i] this is pretty self explanitory. If the playername equals Carn Carn and the player rights are biggerthan or equal to 1 then do everything within '{' and '}' but if it doesnt it skips everything within '{' and '}'unless there is an else if..

the next two lines teleport the player to the desired location...

this line: [i]else if(playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("D E C O Y") && isNoob() == true)[/i] is what it will read if the playername isnt carn carn and the rights aren't >= 1 and again, if it doesn't then it skips

here is an easy way of putting this if statement that might let you understand easyer ;)

[code]If (playername = "CarN CarN") And (playerrights >= 1) Then
            Me.teleportToX = 241
	    me.teleportToY = 241
        ElseIf (playername = "D E C O Y") And (isNoob) Then
            Me.CanhaveChildren = False
        End If [/code]

the 'then' is the '{' and the End if is the '}' i hope this is easy to understand, and helps you :)


